\begin_layout Plain Layout
A Persistent Puzzle
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
Some sovereigns face persistently high spreads despite moderate debt and improving fundamentals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
Event evidence (e.g.,
 Argentina’s inflation misreporting) shows spread decoupling beyond direct balance-sheet effects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
Standard models struggle to match elevated average premia with lower volatility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame

\series bold
This paper
\series default
:
 a single pricing operator with a second-moment belief wedge (PRO) that 
\emph on
pivots
\emph default
 price/spread schedules.
\end_layout

