\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
PRO Mechanism:

\series default
 Lenders overweight policy dispersion 
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow$
\end_inset

 bond-price pivot around a state-dependent threshold 
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow$
\end_inset

 safe states cheaper for lenders,
 risky states 
\emph on
softening of doom
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Comparative statics:

\series default
 Higher default thresholds,
 deleveraging yet higher average spreads (
\emph on
stability illusion
\emph default
),
 welfare loss 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
RI microfoundation:

\series default
 Optimal attention to dispersion 
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow$
\end_inset

 
\series bold
state-dependent
\series default
 tail weight of 
\emph on
default
\emph default
 entering the same operator
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Policy & information:

\series default
 Limits of fiscal transfers;
 negativity-biased learning persistence;
 transparency improves welfare
\end_layout

